text: Zeyno Günenç (born June 22, 1967, İzmit) is a theater, cinema and serialist. == Biography == Zeyno Günenç graduated from Mimar Sinan University State Conservatory Theater Department. She worked in Bursa State Theater for three years. She resigned from this institution and went to Vancouver. Süheyl Uygur and Behzat Uygur brothers traveled to Turkey for a three-year tour of the game titled "Three Slakers". Famous with the character "Aunt Dominant Gonul" in the series named Çocuklar Duymasın ("Children's Hearing"). She married Okan Bayülgen and worked in the Tiyatrokare community. It was alleged that some of the morning program at TRT broke down due to pressures. == Filmography == *Tatlı İntikam - 2016 * Çocuklar Duymasın - 2010 * Geniş Aile - 2009 * Paramparça Aşklar - 2008 * Hayat Apartmanı - 2007 * Doktorlar - 2006 * Keloğlan Kara Prens'e Karşı - 2005 * Çocuklar Ne Olacak - 2004 * Avrupa Yakası - 2004 * Çocuklar Duymasın - 2002 * En Son Babalar Duyar - 2002 * Dadı - 2001 * Eyvah Kızım Büyüdü - 2000 * Kuşlu Çorap - 1988 == References == ==Other websites== * Category:1967 births Category:Living people Category:Turkish actors
